Subject: winex11: always advertise MWM_FUNC_CLOSE in the Motif
 hints

Live's main window is WS_DISABLED while its startup modal is up.  When
the window is mapped during that phase, set_mwm_hints omits
MWM_FUNC_CLOSE, and KWin (which derives closeability from the Motif
function list, unlike the min/max buttons) shows a titlebar without a
close button.  The hints refresh on EnableWindow can be swallowed by
the desired/pending state tracking, so the desired hints sit unflushed
until the next WM state round trip; maximizing triggers
window_request_desired_state and the button appears, which is the
exact symptom of issue #31.

The close button is never hidden on Windows, disabled window or not,
and handle_wm_protocols already drops WM_DELETE_WINDOW while the
window is disabled, so advertising the function unconditionally
changes nothing for modal correctness.  It removes the dependency on
hint-refresh timing entirely.

Fixes shibco/ableton-linux#31.
---
 dlls/winex11.drv/window.c | 11 +++++++++--
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winex11.drv/window.c b/dlls/winex11.drv/window.c
index adcbeb8e..8bd2c7e3 100644
--- a/dlls/winex11.drv/window.c
+++ b/dlls/winex11.drv/window.c
@@ -1104,11 +1104,18 @@ static void set_mwm_hints( struct x11drv_win_data *data, UINT style, UINT ex_sty
     else
     {
         mwm_hints.decorations = get_mwm_decorations( data, style, ex_style );
-        mwm_hints.functions = MWM_FUNC_MOVE;
+        /* Always advertise the close function: Windows never hides the titlebar
+         * close button, even on a disabled window.  KWin removes the button when
+         * MWM_FUNC_CLOSE is absent, so hints computed during a WS_DISABLED phase
+         * (Ableton Live's main window while its startup modal is up) leave the
+         * button missing until the next hints flush, which may not happen until
+         * the user maximizes.  Modal correctness is preserved regardless:
+         * handle_wm_protocols drops WM_DELETE_WINDOW while the window is
+         * disabled, so the visible button is a no-op, same as on Windows. */
+        mwm_hints.functions = MWM_FUNC_MOVE | MWM_FUNC_CLOSE;
         if (is_window_resizable( data, style )) mwm_hints.functions |= MWM_FUNC_RESIZE;
         if (!(style & WS_DISABLED))
         {
-            mwm_hints.functions |= MWM_FUNC_CLOSE;
             if (style & WS_MINIMIZEBOX) mwm_hints.functions |= MWM_FUNC_MINIMIZE;
             if (style & WS_MAXIMIZEBOX) mwm_hints.functions |= MWM_FUNC_MAXIMIZE;
 
